      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VARIUS (10) improved last start, beaten only 1.1 lengths over 1500m at Port Macquarie, after being prominent at the turn. Should be hitting this at peak fitness and has strong prospects. PEAR BELLINI (6)  is backing up just six days after she was strongly fancied over 1505m at Tuncurry on a heavy track, but found one much too good. Has a 4kg claim today and can make amends on a less onerous surface. TAKETHEMONEYANDRUN (4) has been around the mark without winning. Better suited today and coming back to 1600m. Maps well and won't be far away. VEGA SICILIA (5) ran an improved race at Port Macquarie and can't be ruled out back 215m. Has an inside barrier and 2kg claim and has plenty of scope for improvement.",
